atform evidence.","Research, publication, or PhD-style framing.","Consumer-scale or multi-cloud breadth claims without explicit metrics and scope."],"safe_positioning":["Show architecture ownership, integration depth, and production reliability because architecture is the strongest evidence type in 20 deep-analysis samples and platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%).","Show collaboration and mentoring as force multipliers because collaboration appears in 23/25 roles (92%) and mentoring in 12/25 (48%).","Show AI delivery through shipped systems, evaluation, and guardrails because agents_orchestration appears in 12/25 (48%), RAG in 9/25 (36%), evaluation_quality in 5/25 (20%), and guardrails_governance in 7/25 (28%)."],"unsafe_positioning":["Do not imply direct hiring authority or formal people management unless the CV proves it; hiring appears in 2/25 roles (8%) and performance management in 1/25 (4%).","Do not imply research-heavy credentials; research_heavy_pct and requires_phd_pct are both 0/25 (0%).","Do not claim direct MCP, OpenAI, Anthropic, HIPAA, or full multi-cloud implementation unless explicitly documented; these are named in unsafe_claims_top despite low direct frequency."],"citations":["Soft skills: collaboration 23/25 (92%), mentoring 12/25 (48%), communication 10/25 (40%).","AI stack: agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%), RAG 9/25 (36%), evaluation_quality 5/25 (20%), guardrails_governance 7/25 (28%).","Management and disqualifiers: hiring 2/25 (8%), performance_management 1/25 (4%), research_heavy_pct 0/25 (0%), requires_phd_pct 0/25 (0%)."]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture And Platforms","themes":[{"theme":"AI platform architecture and system design","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category is architecture-led. Show end-to-end design ownership for production systems, reusable platforms, and integration boundaries because platform design appears in 24/25 roles (96%) and architecture is the top valued evidence type in 20 deep-analysis samples.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: platform architecture, system design, AI platform. Use 2-3 mentions across headline/profile/experience/skills. Secondary keywords: greenfield, modernization. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche vendor names once only.","citation":"Platform design 24/25 (96%); valued evidence type architecture 20 deep-analysis samples."},{"theme":"Distributed systems and cloud-native backend foundations","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This market still screens for deep backend and distributed systems judgment under the AI layer. Show service boundaries, event-driven systems, APIs, and scalable backend delivery because distributed systems appears in 7/25 roles (28%) and backend engineering, CI/CD, and Kubernetes each appear in 4/25 (16%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: distributed systems, backend engineering. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: event-driven systems, cloud-native systems, Kubernetes, CI/CD. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche language or cloud terms once only.","citation":"Hard skills: distributed systems 7/25 (28%), backend engineering 4/25 (16%), CI/CD 4/25 (16%), Kubernetes 4/25 (16%), event-driven systems 3/25 (12%), cloud-native systems 3/25 (12%)."},{"theme":"System integration and modernization under enterprise constraints","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The hiring pain points point to integration complexity, modernization, and solution selection through POCs. Show cases where you connected AI or cloud services into existing enterprise systems and improved code quality or delivery safety.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: system integration, modernization, proof of concept, enterprise systems. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche domain terms once only and only if true.","citation":"Pain points are repeated as single-sample signals: integration across multiple systems (1), choose appropriate solutions through POCs (1), modernize and improve code quality while integrating AI services (1)."}]},{"section_name":"Production AI Delivery","themes":[{"theme":"Agent orchestration and reusable AI workflow systems","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"This category is more platform-and-orchestration oriented than generic LLM feature work. Show shipped agent workflows, reusable tool integrations, orchestration logic, and developer-facing enablement because agents_orchestration appears in 12/25 roles (48%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: agent orchestration, AI workflows. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: developer tools, reusable platform, plugins. Use 1-2 mentions. Framework names only once and only if true.","citation":"AI stack signals: agents_orchestration 12/25 (48%); frameworks are fragmented, with LangChain highest at 5/25 (20%)."},{"theme":"RAG, retrieval, and vector-based grounding","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Retrieval-driven delivery is a visible category pattern, but not universal. Show grounded-answering systems, retrieval quality work, embeddings, and vector search only when you have production evidence because RAG appears in 9/25 (36%) and vector_search in 5/25 (20%).","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: RAG, retrieval, vector databases. Use 2-3 mentions for one or two core terms. Secondary keywords: embeddings, vector search. Use 1-2 mentions. Database brand names once only.","citation":"AI stack signals: RAG 9/25 (36%), vector_search 5/25 (20%); hard skills: vector databases 5/25 (20%), embeddings 4/25 (16%)."},{"theme":"Evaluation, guardrails, and production quality controls","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"This category values AI quality and safe production behavior more than generic prompt claims. Show eval harnesses, structured output validation, hallucination handling, guardrails, and governance where delivered because evaluation_quality appears in 5/25 (20%) and guardrails_governance in 7/25 (28%).","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: evaluation, guardrails, structured output validation, governance. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche compliance labels once only and only if directly supported.","citation":"AI stack signals: evaluation_quality 5/25 (20%), guardrails_governance 7/25 (28%); deep-analysis success metrics include handling hallucinations (1) and structured output validation (1)."}]},{"section_name":"Reliability And Operations","themes":[{"theme":"Reliability, observability, and production hardening","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Production reliability is central to this category. Show uptime, incident reduction, latency stability, failure handling, and observability instrumentation because reliability is cited in 18 deep-analysis samples, observability appears in 6/25 roles (24%), and reliability is the top success metric cluster.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords if true: reliability, observability, production. Use 2-3 mentions. Secondary keywords: incident response, SLOs, monitoring. Use 1-2 mentions only if you truly owned them. Tool names once only.","citation":"Valued evidence types: reliability 18 deep-analysis samples; hard skills: observability 6/25 (24%); success metrics: reliability appears 4 times, performance 3 times, scalability 2 times."},{"theme":"Cloud deployment and delivery discipline","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Cloud and deployment tooling matter, but the sample does not support over-optimizing around one vendor. Show deployment rigor, containerization, and delivery systems when they are real, while keeping vendor claims narrow because multi_cloud appears in 8 samples, AWS in 4, and GCP in 2.","ats_guidance":"Secondary keywords if true: AWS, GCP, Kubernetes, CI/CD. Use 1-2 mentions. Niche provider services once only. Do not force multi-cloud wording unless the CV proves more than one cloud.","citation":"Architecture cloud preference: multi_cloud 8 samples, AWS 4, GCP 2; hard skills: Kubernetes 4/25 (16%), CI/